column5: What changes are you making to your trip for next year?

Two trips to Lac Seul next year. The trip with the guys is moving from late September to the opener to accomodate scheduling difficulties in September. And the trip with my wife is moving from the last week in May to the third week in August to get away from snow & frost! 170 days but who's counting? Have a great Thanksgiving holiday. We all have so much to remember and be thankful for. Lars
Instead of 11 weeks this summer will be at least 12 weeks.
Two weeks in May. Two or three weeks in August. Two weeks in October. Missed a fall trip this year and I'm hurting because of it.
Might stay 2 weeks instead of 10 days. End of June. Other wise no changes.
I'll be going back to Wiley Point with my dad for the second year in a row with him and my fifth trip there. He loved the place since I took him for his birthday last year.
We are going to take one of ours members son in this year. Time to get the younger generation into the flyin way of fishing.
